      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 2160: The retry timer can fire after the account has unregistered or entered a new registration state; the handler only checks that accountManager_ still exists before calling startSync(). That can restart sync/presence publishing for an account that is no longer registered, especially if unregister does not reset identityRetryState_. Add a registration/DHT-running guard in the timer callback before retrying.\n```suggestion\n                        if (acc-\u003eaccountManager_ \u0026\u0026 acc-\u003edht_ \u0026\u0026 acc-\u003edht_-\u003eisRunning()\n                            \u0026\u0026 acc-\u003egetRegistrationState() \u003d\u003d RegistrationState::REGISTERED) {\n```",
