      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2739: Calling presenceManager_-\u003erefresh() on every connectivityChanged() while the DHT is running can also run on non-recovery connectivity events, causing all tracked presence subscriptions to be torn down and recreated unnecessarily. On mobile networks this can happen frequently and may create extra DHT listen churn and transient presence gaps. Gate the refresh to the actual transition where the DHT/account has come back online after being unavailable, or debounce it through the existing account/connection state machinery.\n```suggestion\n    if (presenceManager_ \u0026\u0026 dht_ \u0026\u0026 dht_-\u003eisRunning() \u0026\u0026 isRegistered())\n        presenceManager_-\u003erefresh();\n```",
